
Goal: Search for users by their name using the GitHub API (sorted by the number of followers) and display the
username, avatar_url and repos_url in a table.

UX Flow:
1- Type the full name of the user, like Ben Lesh, Jake Wharton, Krunoslav Zaherand, and so on.
2- Show results as the user types the name without them having to press a search button.

How to Use:

1. Install the required dependencies using npm: npm install

2. Start the development server: npm start

3. Open your browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000 to search users by thir name.



